timetraveller (1.5.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * debian/control: declare pkexec explicitly. Depends listed
    "polkitd | policykit-1", but since Debian 12 / Ubuntu 23.04 the old
    policykit-1 package was split and polkitd ships only the daemon --
    /usr/bin/pkexec is now its own binary package. A minimal install could
    satisfy every declared dependency and still have no pkexec, breaking
    every privileged helper path (system backup, delete, maintain, crontab
    install, config write). The alternation "pkexec | policykit-1" also
    covers older releases where policykit-1 still shipped the binary.
  * debian/control: recommend a graphical polkit authentication agent. It is
    Recommends rather than Depends because GNOME's agent lives inside
    gnome-shell and Provides: nothing, so no alternation can express "this
    desktop already has one"; pkexec falls back to its own textual agent for
    CLI use regardless.
  * Fix stale __version__ leaking a wrong version into archive provenance.
    timetraveller/__init__.py still said 1.5.0 while the changelog and
    pyproject.toml said 1.5.3. Not cosmetic: worker.py stamps archives with
    created_by=f"timetraveller {__version__}", so every archive written by
    v1.5.1 through v1.5.3 falsely claims it was created by 1.5.0. The version
    lives in three places, not the two the release process assumed.

