timetraveller (1.5.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Archives cleanup pass -- three fixes to the archive browser/search:
    - Source-mode search/browse divergence: the cross-archive search read the
      local sidecar mirror while the browse tree read the browsed directory in
      restore-from-anywhere (source) mode, so their results could disagree.
      Search now reads the same sidecar source the browse tree uses per mode,
      and stats the sidecar file rather than trusting the manifest's
      (possibly stale) has_sidecar flag.
    - Extract button vs. visible selection: the bottom "Extract selected..."
      button acts on the browse tree, but stayed visible while the search page
      (which has its own extract button) was shown. It is now hidden while
      searching, so the only exposed extract always matches what is on screen.
    - Blank file tree after search: opening an archive and switching to search
      before its sidecar finished loading set the tree model on a hidden
      QStackedWidget page, leaving the uniform-height rows un-laid-out, so the
      browse pane came back blank and would not repopulate. The view is now
      relaid out when the browse page becomes visible again, and blanking the
      tree clears the current-set guard so a reselect always reloads.

