timetraveller (1.4.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: the last two GUI worker actions that didn't escalate on system-class
    plans -- reindex (rebuild a missing .idx.zst sidecar) and recover-failed
    (un-quarantine a failed-but-intact backup). Both run via the archive panel's
    job tracker as the unprivileged user and would fail writing the root-owned
    sidecar/manifest. They now self-escalate (_needs_root_escalation) through a
    new combined pkexec helper timetraveller-maintain-system-archive (+ policy
    com.timetraveller.maintain-system-archive), which validates the plan
    allowlist, the action (--reindex/--recover-failed), and a strict archive-
    filename identifier (charset, no traversal, must end .pax.zst; bare `*`
    accepted only for --reindex), then re-execs the canonical binary against the
    root-owned /etc config. Mirror resynced afterward. This closes the
    "privileged plan + unprivileged GUI" class: backup, delete, schedule,
    reindex and recover all escalate now.

